Chinese relatives of passengers on board missing flight MH370 have travelled to Malaysia in search of answers. The group of 32 family members are angry and frustrated at what they claim is a lack of new information from authorities, more than three weeks after the Malaysia Airlines plane disappeared. The airline flew them from Beijing to Kuala Lumpur - the reverse of the route the missing Boeing 777 was on when it vanished from radar screens. They now plan to meet top officials in the